      "writtenOn": "2020-04-22T14:55:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I think for now I plan on leaving this as is. As you said currently it is only tied to the number of textures in a given shader. Thus I expect this like to be about size 4 (0, 1, 2, 3) textures. Quickly looking through 4 options will be very fast. I thought about the count being an index into an array, but it gets a little weird since we don\u0027t really have a bounds on the number of textures we may use in a shader (outside hardware limits). So for the very few variations we have in practice I can\u0027t imagine quickly checking the maybe ~4 items will be too much of a perf lost compared to direct indexing. But happy to do this if you think it will be worth it.\n\nOnce we move away from using spirv and spirv-cross I think it will allow us to be a lot more flexible in how we want to set up these root signatures and possible use other types of descriptors. Once we do that I agree that going more to a key and map based system would be better if we think we\u0027ll get a lot of different variations. But in the short term I don\u0027t think the overhead of setting up that system is worth it for now.",
      "parentUuid": "83c60a54_f23dce65",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 9,
